The paper focuses on using app store data and crowd-generated information to identify key features of applications in a particular domain, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the potential benefits for practitioners (e.g. software developers) in using this approach, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper touches on the use of machine learning to elicit automated requirements, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
